<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Schreiber is a Hoffman Wannabe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Dustin Hoffman was behind the scenes in the  
recent movie ``A Walk on the Moon,'' but was actor Liev Schreiber 
doing a Hoffman impression on-screen? 
</P>
<P>
	``Well, you know, he told me that when I first met him,''  
Hoffman said Monday night on NPR's ``Fresh Air'' show. ``He says, 
`You know, I've been ripping you off since the beginning.''' 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffman is co-producer of the movie, which takes on life in a  
Jewish vacation spot in the Catskills in the summer of 1969 -- the 
year of Woodstock and the first walk on the moon. 
</P>
<P>
	Schreiber and Diane Lane play a working-class New York couple  
who get caught up in the times. 
</P>
<P>
	Tony Goldwyn, the grandson of Samuel Goldwyn, was Hoffman's  
co-producer and directed the movie. He joked to ``Fresh Air'' host 
Terry Gross that he coached Schreiber to mimic Hoffman. 
</P>
<P>
	```Liev, it's really good, but if you could, just on this take,  
a little bit more like Dustin that would be great. I think what 
Dustin would do at this moment is ...'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hoffman: ``That's all you have to do, is tell an actor that. ...  
He's producing it, and we'll only let you play the part if you do 
him.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
