<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Illinois St. Guard To Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Illinois State point guard Victor Williams,  
the Missouri Valley Conference's Freshman of the Year, said Tuesday 
he will transfer to another college at the end of the school year. 
</P>
<P>
	The 5-foot-10 Williams averaged 7.9 points and 3.3 assists a  
game last season, when he started 25 of the Redbirds' 31 games. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams said he wanted to be closer to his home in Kansas City.  
</P>
<P>
	Former assistant Tom Richardson took over earlier this month as  
head coach after Kevin Stallings left for Vanderbilt. But Williams 
said he had been thinking about a transfer for a few months. 
</P>
