<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Otis Thorpe Grabs 10,000th Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Otis Thorpe grabbed his 10,000th rebound Tuesday  
night, becoming the 16th player in NBA history to score at least 
15,000 points and get 10,000 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	The Washington Wizards forward entered the game against the  
Chicago Bulls needing two rebounds to reach 10,000. Thorpe, 36, got 
his first with 5:50 left in the first quarter, when he grabbed an 
offensive rebound and put it back for a basket. 
</P>
<P>
	The 10,000th came off the defensive board with 2:39 left in the  
first. The game wasn't stopped. 
</P>
<P>
	Thorpe finished the game with nine rebounds and six points.  
</P>
<P>
	``Those are the things that happen when you hang around for  
awhile and work at your game and work hard,'' he said. ``Work 
within the system that you've been involved in, good things happen 
for you.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The others in the 15,000-10,000 club are: Kareem Abdul-Jabbar,  
Wilt Chamberlain, Karl Malone, Moses Malone, Elvin Hayes, Hakeem 
Olajuwon, Robert Parish, Elgin Baylor, Charles Barkley, Walt 
Bellamy, Bob Pettit, Dolph Schayes, Jack Sikma, Buck Williams and 
Patrick Ewing. Of the 15, 12 are on the NBA's list of 50 greatest 
players. 
</P>
<P>
	Ewing got his 10,000th rebound earlier this season.  
</P>
<P>
	``You're talking about legendary players, guys who have gone out  
there and set the foundation. Just to be a part of that group is a 
great achievement,'' Thorpe said. ``It's nice to be a part of that 
club.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Thorpe, in his 15th NBA season, entered the game with 17,042  
points. He was the 55th player to reach 17,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
