<HEADLINE> Tolme Named AP Correspondent in Va. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SPRINGFIELD, Va. (AP) -- Paul Tolme, a newsman in the Providence,  
R.I., bureau of The Associated Press, has been named AP's 
correspondent in Springfield, Va. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Tuesday by Virginia Chief of  
Bureau Dorothy Abernathy. 
</P>
<P>
	Tolme joined the AP in Concord, N.H., in 1989, transferred to  
Portland, Maine, for 10 months in 1991 and then returned to New 
Hampshire. He transferred to Providence in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Tolme, 33, is a native of Tilton, N.H., and a graduate of the  
University of New Hampshire. 
