foot along the city's waterfront has been given the boot. 
</P>
<P>
	The 18-foot-tall stainless-steel foot had won the unanimous  
approval of the city's Art Commission. 
</P>
<P>
	But since then, many San Franciscans have blasted the artwork as  
inappropriate and a waste of the $500,000 it would cost taxpayers. 
City supervisors rejected the project with a 6-4 vote on Monday. 
</P>
