<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pastor To Lead Same-Sex Union Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- A United Methodist pastor ordered suspended for  
blessing the ``marriage'' of two Chicago men will become director 
of a group working to lift the church's ban on same-sex unions. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rev. Gregory Dell, pastor at Broadway United Methodist  
Church in Chicago, said he will become director of the group ``In 
All Things Charity'' when his suspension takes effect July 5. 
</P>
<P>
	``There are just a whole lot of clergy out there that have been  
caught not just in this law, but in others that have affected gay 
and lesbian clergy as well,'' he said Tuesday of the church law 
banning same-sex unions. 
</P>
<P>
	The group, which has members throughout the Methodist church,  
was founded in 1997 and counts Dell's church among its sponsors, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Until now, however, the group has had no staff. Dell says the  
group hopes to raise money to pay for him to travel and speak to 
Methodist pastors and members nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
	A jury of Methodist pastors in the church's Northern Illinois  
Conference last month ordered Dell suspended for deliberately 
disobeying church law when he presided over a same-sex union in 
September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
