<HEADLINE> Sandy Duncan Replaced in `Chicago' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- It's Ann Reinking to the rescue.  
</P>
<P>
	The dancer-choreographer joins the touring company of  
``Chicago'' next week in Boston to replace Sandy Duncan, who broke 
her foot while rehearsing to take the musical on the road. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Duncan plans to join the New York cast as Roxie Hart when  
her injury heals, said Pete Sanders, a spokesman for the show. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am very disappointed at not being able to perform in Boston  
as it is one of my favorite theater cities,'' Ms. Duncan said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Reinking originally starred in and choreographed the revival  
of ``Chicago,'' which opened in New York in November 1996. She will 
play in Boston through May 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
