<HEADLINE> L.L. Bean Recalls Backpack Carriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FREEPORT, Maine (AP) -- L.L. Bean is recalling about 13,000  
backpack child carriers after getting about 25 reports of children 
slipping out of leg openings or falling out the top and getting 
hurt, the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission says. 
</P>
<P>
	The recall involves the W695 model. The backpacks are teal with  
gray harnesses and kickstands used to prop the bags up while 
loading children. 
</P>
<P>
	They were sold for $95 through L.L. Bean's catalog and Web site  
and at stores in New Hampshire, Delaware, Oregon and Maine between 
1993 and 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	The model number is on a tag.  
</P>
<P>
	Last December, L.L. Bean recalled 10,000 of the AC25 model  
child-carrier backpack, which had similar problems as the W695. 
</P>
<P>
                            	 *------	 
</P>
<P>
	Customers can get refund information by calling the company at 1  
(800) 555-9717, or from the company's Web site at 
www.llbean.com/recall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
