<HEADLINE> Boys Charged With Raping Woman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Five boys have been charged with  
raping a 21-year-old mentally retarded woman. 
</P>
<P>
	The boys, ranging in age from 12 to 16, were being held in  
juvenile detention, were charged with sexual battery on a mentally 
impaired person. 
</P>
<P>
	The woman told police that four of the boys raped her as another  
boy cheered them on after she went to a neighbor's home to speak 
with the grandmother who lived there. 
</P>
<P>
	One of the boys pulled her inside, locked the door and began  
touching her, then pulled her to the floor, she told police. 
</P>
<P>
	Sabrina Gibson, mother of one of the suspects arrested Friday,  
said the boys told her the woman came into the house on her own. 
</P>
<P>
	``She started taking her clothes off, saying, 'It's hot, it's  
hot,''' Gibson said. ``They tried to tell her to get out. She 
wouldn't get out.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Gibson said the boys told her they didn't touch the woman, and  
she left the home. 
</P>
