<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Close Mixed / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stock prices closed mixed Tuesday after  
languishing in negative territory for most of the session. The U.S. 
dollar was lower against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 117.98 yen at midafternoon, down 0.18 yen from  
late Monday in Tokyo but above its late New York level of 117.58 
yen overnight. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average rose 22.90 points,  
or 0.14 percent, to close the day at 16,697.11. On Monday, the 
index lost 177.37 points, or 1.05 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	On the stock market, prices recouped early losses as foreign and  
individual investors poured funds into the Japanese market. A 
tumble in hi-tech issues, triggered by a selloff of technology 
shares in New York, had kept the Tokyo market lower for most of the 
session. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wall Street, the technology-laden Nasdaq Composite Index lost  
138.43 points Monday to 2,345.61 for its second steepest drop ever. 
The Dow Jones industrial average fell after five straight sessions 
of record highs, slipping 53.36 points, or 0.5 percent to 
10,440.53. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
exchange's first section was down 3.79 points, or 0.28 percent, to 
1,328.90. The TOPIX lost 10.34 points, or 0.77 percent, the 
previous day. 
</P>
<P>
	In currency dealings, the dollar edged higher from levels  
overnight in New York, mainly on technical gains as U.S. funds 
bought euros against the yen to cover short, or oversold, 
positions. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar was also supported as both Japanese Finance Minister  
Kiichi Miyazawa and the ministry's international bureau head 
Haruhiko Kuroda expressed displeasure at the recent strengthening 
of the yen against the dollar. 
</P>
<P>
	In other major currencies, the euro was traded at 125.98 yen, up  
from 125.87 yen late Monday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark No. 211 10-year Japanese government  
bond dropped to 1.485 percent from Monday's close of 1.575 percent, 
driving its price up to 102.78 yen from 101.97 yen. 
</P>
<P>
 *(may-js-dj) 
</P>
</TEXT>
