<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Tech Stocks Recover; Dow Up 8.02  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were mostly higher today, as  
technology stocks recovered from yesterday's rout but industrial 
companies, also changing course, fell amid profit-taking. The Dow 
industrials closed up 8.02 at 10,448.55 after fluctuating between 
positive and negative territory throughout the session. The Nasdaq, 
which is heavily weighted with technology names, rose 64.04 to 
2,409.65, after having plunged 138 points yesterday. Internet 
shares were back in favor, including Amazon.com and AOL, which rose 
sharply. AOL stock was up 12 5/8 at 128 1/2, and Amazon.com was up 13 1/6 
at 172. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 was up 16 today. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,448.55  +  8.02
