chief executive, the company purchased a full-page advertisement 
published today in two newspapers promising customers and 
shareholders it is committed to rebuilding. Chief executive Eckhard 
Pfeiffer was asked to resign after Compaq announced it anticipated 
earnings of 15 cents per share in the first quarter on revenue of 
$9.4 billion -- $600 million lower than expected. 

