</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- America's trade deficit soared more than 15  
percent to a record $19.4 billion in February as the global 
financial crisis depressed U.S. exports for a fourth straight month 
while booming consumer demand pushed imports to an all-time high. 
U.S. exports edged down 0.6 percent to $76.6 billion. Imports 
jumped 2.3 percent to an all-time high of $96 billion as demand for 
foreign cars, clothing, toys, televisions and stereos soared. 

</P>
