brands like Mattel and Hasbro, and specialty names like Brio and 
Creativity for Kids. Analysts told USA Today that eToys hopes the 
content-heavy site of San Francisco-based BabyCenter will drive 
sales as moms using BabyCenter will turn to eToys to buy toys for 
toddlers. 

