<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton's Commencement Itinerary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton will address the 1999  
graduating classes of the U.S. Air Force Academy, the University of 
Chicago and Louisiana's Grambling State University, the White House 
announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	By tradition, the president annually delivers commencement  
addresses to one of the nation's military academies, one private 
school and one public school. Clinton will travel to Grambling, 
La., for the May 23 graduation ceremonies at Grambling State, to 
the Air Force Academy in Colorado Springs, Colo., on June 2, and to 
the University of Chicago on June 12. 
</P>
<P>
	Last year, Clinton spoke to graduates at the Naval Academy, the  
Massachusetts Institute of Technology, and Portland State 
University in Oregon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
