<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 17:52:33 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Giants' Hayes Suspended for 4 Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- San Francisco Giants third baseman Charlie Hayes  
was suspended for four games by the National League on Tuesday for 
charging Arizona pitcher Todd Stottlemyre from second base last 
week and instigating a brawl. 
</P>
<P>
	Hayes and Stottlemyre were also fined $2,000 each by NL  
president Len Coleman. Hayes decided not to appeal the penalty, and 
started serving the penalty Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``I got four games and I'm taking it now,'' Hayes said. ``That's  
all I've got to say.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Stottlemyre said he will not appeal the fine.  
</P>
<P>
	``I really don't want to agree or disagree with it. I just want  
to put it behind me. I think it's best for me to put it behind me 
and I think it's best for the club not to become an obstacle 
through an appeal process or anything like that,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm not sure I disagree or agree with how it was done. But I'm  
going to accept it and pay the fine and move on. That's probably 
the best scenario for everybody,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Stottlemyre was still surprised the whole incident occurred.  
</P>
<P>
	``How they rule on him I don't want to make an opinion one way  
or another. I think the whole situation probably shouldn't have 
happened but it did,'' he said. ``I think it did because in the 
heat of battle he was obviously frustrated and wanted to take out 
some of his frustrations.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hayes charged the mound from second base in the sixth inning at  
Phoenix last Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't land a punch, but I did try to hurt him,'' Hayes said  
after the game. ``He can say `Hi' to me, and I'll try to slap him. 
I just don't like him. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was trying to knock him out,'' Hayes said. ``I didn't want  
to wrestle. He talks like he's Bob Gibson. I'm the only one he can 
get out. ... I'm sick of people like that. Who does he think he is, 
Sandy Koufax or somebody? To me he's a .500 pitcher, 12-and-12. I 
don't think nobody likes him. I don't think some of his teammates 
like him. He's going to get some of them hurt. He needs to just 
pitch and just shut up.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Stottlemyre said this is the first time anyone had gone after  
him from second base. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought he was yelling at me from first base, so when he got  
to second base, I had something to say to him,'' Stottlemyre said. 
``That was enough to trigger him, and here he came. I don't know 
why he was frustrated. I guess you'll have to ask him. ... He 
missed me all night at the plate and he missed me on the mound.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
