<HEADLINE> Washington Mayor To Salute NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Delegates to the NATO Summit will be treated  
to a taste of local food and entertainment at a Saturday night 
reception with Mayor Anthony William as the host. 
</P>
<P>
	Some of the nation's top corporations will foot the bill for the  
$300,000 event as ``Washington Salutes NATO'' during the Atlantic 
alliance's 50th anniversary celebration. 
</P>
<P>
	``We'll highlight the diversity of the district's  
neighborhoods,'' said Kay McGrath, special assistant to the mayor. 
``We've arranged for local groups to provide the entertainment.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The National Building Museum will be divided into sections  
representing different areas of the city. 
</P>
<P>
	--The trendy Adams Morgan area will feature the Latin Jazz band  
``Bossa Lingo'' and various Mexican and Caribbean dishes. 
</P>
<P>
	--An area celebrating the predominately black Anacostia section  
will feature performances by the Urban Nation Voices of Youth and 
the H.I.P. H.O.P. Choir. The menu there will include peanut chicken 
and black-eyed pea salad. 
</P>
<P>
	--Capitol Hill's contribution includes a menu featuring crested  
tenderloin of beef, Caesar salad and pasta, with entertainment 
provided by the Navy's Commodore's Combo jazz band. 
</P>
<P>
	--The Chinatown area will feature Oriental cuisine, while Embassy  
Row will be celebrated with a variety of desserts. 
</P>
<P>
	Invited guests include the 1,700 delegates to the NATO  
conference and about 200 of the district's political and civic 
leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
