<HEADLINE>  Israelis Remember War Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JERUSALEM (AP) --Traffic stopped and Israelis stepped out of  
their cars on streets and highways Tuesday to remember soldiers 
fallen in battle and countrymen killed in terror attacks. 
</P>
<P>
	Sirens sounded across the country at 11 a.m., signaling the  
start of two minutes of silence on a day of mourning for fallen 
loved ones. 
</P>
<P>
	Flags flew at half-staff, and radio and television stations  
broadcast mournful songs and interviews with the families of men 
and women who lost their lives during compulsory military service. 
</P>
<P>
	``We come here to unite and remember,'' Prime Minister Benjamin  
