draped in a shawl stooped over a grave, sobbing. 
</P>
<P>
	Across town at the Cinematheque cafe, a young woman dressed in  
bright summer colors set down her orange juice and stood to gaze 
across the valley of Gehenna at the Old City walls -- the site of 
fierce battles in the 1967 and 1948 wars. She wept. 
