<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) --The dollar was mixed against other major currencies  
in European trading today. Gold rose.	
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0663, up from $1.0634 Monday. The  
dollar bought 117.77 Japanese yen, up from 117.75 yen. At midday in 
New York, the euro was quoted at $1.0622 and the dollar was quoted 
at 118.22 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Monday: 1.5027  
Swiss francs, down from 1.5060; 1.4873 Canadian dollars, up from 
1.4801. The British pound was quoted at $1.6176, down from $1.6215. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth: 1.8342 German marks, down from 1.8392; 
6.1517 French francs, down from 6.1685; 2.0667 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0723; 1,815.88 Italian lire, down from 1,820.83. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $284.40 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$283.60 on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $283.95, up from $283.65.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose $0.10 in Hong Kong to close at $284.85.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.17 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$5.10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
