<HEADLINE> O'Neal Ejected After 2nd Technical </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Los Angeles Lakers center Shaquille  
O'Neal, the NBA's leading scorer, was ejected after drawing his 
second technical foul late in the second quarter of Tuesday night's 
game against Golden State. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Neal's second technical followed a shoving match on the court  
with 3:09 left in the period. 
</P>
<P>
	Golden State guard Bimbo Coles and Lakers forward Robert Horry  
were jawing with each other at midcourt when Coles suddenly pushed 
Horry. O'Neal came up from behind and shoved Coles. Teammates from 
both sides rushed in to restrain O'Neal and Coles, preventing an 
escalation. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Neal was then led off the court into the locker room.  
</P>
<P>
	Coles also was hit with a technical, his first of the game.  
</P>
<P>
	O'Neal was called for his first technical earlier in the second  
for arguing with officials in the aftermatch of a collision between 
Kobe Bryant and Golden State center Felton Spencer. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time of his departure, O'Neal had 10 points and four  
rebounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
