<HEADLINE> Clinton Nominates Ambassadors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton nominated two veteran  
diplomats to ambassadorships in Nicaragua and Ecuador Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton said he was sending to the Senate for confirmation the  
nominations of Gwen C. Clare as ambassador to Ecuador and Oliver P. 
Garza as ambassador to Nicaragua. 
</P>
<P>
	Clare, a native of Hilton Head Island, S.C., and graduate of the  
National War College, has served in Portugal, Chile, Peru, El 
Salvador and Brazil since entering the foreign service in 1967. 
</P>
<P>
	Garza is the U.S. consul general in Guadalajara, Mexico.  
Previous postings for the 28-year veteran of the foreign service 
include deputy chief of mission in Bogota, Colombia, and Panama. 
</P>
