<HEADLINE> Finland Jobless Rate at 10.9 Pct. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HELSINKI, Finland (AP) -- Finland's unemployment rate rose to  
10.9 percent in March, up from 10.2 percent in December 1998, the 
government statistics agency said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Last year in March, 12.4 percent of the workforce was out of a  
job, Statistics Finland said. 
</P>
<P>
	The latest figure means that 271,000 people were out of work in  
a population of 5.1 million, making the Finnish rate one of the 
highest in the 15-nation European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
