<DOCNO> APW19990420.0325 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 17:42:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Telecom Italia Supports Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROME (AP) -- Telecom Italia SpA's board of directors on Tuesday  
agreed in principle to a merger with Germany's Deutsche Telekom AG, 
but several major issues still must be resolved. 
</P>
<P>
	Following a seven-hour board meeting, Telecom Italia released a  
statement saying it supports a ``business combination agreement'' 
under which a new company would be set up to combine the two 
companies. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecom Italia did not disclose any financial details of the  
deal it favored. The company has been negotiating with Deutsche 
Telekom in an effort to thwart a hostile takeover bid from its 
smaller Italian rival, Olivetti SpA. 
</P>
<P>
	A combined Telecom Italia and Deutsche Telekom would dwarf its  
competitors in Europe and could become the largest merger in 
history, topping the pending deal between Exxon Corp. and Mobil 
Corp., which was valued Tuesday at about $85 billion, based on the 
price of Exxon stock. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecom Italia stipulated that the agreement would have to be  
``substantially a merger of equals,'' and it did not specify what 
weight each company would have in the new holding company. Analysts 
have speculated that Deutsche Telekom would account for between 56 
percent and 60 percent of the holding company. 
</P>
<P>
	The Italian prime minister's office has said that any accord  
must be on an equal footing, underlining fears in Italy of foreign 
ownership of the strategic telecommunications industry. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecom Italia said its board would give final approval to the  
agreement only when terms are clarified on how the German 
government could limit its voting rights in the company. 
</P>
<P>
	Currently, the German state has a direct and indirect combined  
72 percent stake in Deutsche Telekom, scheduled to diminish to 66 
percent once the German company completes a capital increase some 
time in midsummer. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecom Italia also said an industrial plan for the merged  
entity needed to be worked out before its board could approve the 
deal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990420.0326 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-20 00:12:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Giants' Bonds To Have Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Barry Bonds will undergo surgery on Tuesday  
to repair a bone spur in his left elbow and a damaged triceps 
tendon, San Francisco Giants manager Dusty Baker said Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The All-Star left fielder was placed on the 15-day disabled  
list. There was no indication of how long Bonds would be out of the 
lineup, and the length of his recovery would depend on what the 
surgeons found, general manager Brian Sabean said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think we know yet how long he's going to be out,''  
Sabean said. ``Fortunately it's early in the season. Fortunately 
he's in great shape and has tremendous healing power.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Baker said he learned of the surgery after the victory. Bonds  
was out of the lineup for the second straight day. 
</P>
<P>
	``We just pray that it's not too severe and that he makes a  
quick recovery,'' Baker said after a 5-4 win over Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds, batting .366 with four home runs and 12 RBIs, had an MRI  
on Monday that revealed the bone spur. He decided to get a second 
opinion later in the day from San Jose Sharks physician Dr. Art 
Ting. 
</P>
<P>
	The surgery will be performed by Ting at the Recovery Inn in  
Menlo Park, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
	Stan Javier took Bonds' place in left field, and Ellis Burks  
assumed Bonds' No. 3 spot in the batting order. Burks hit a 
three-run homer in the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
	``When you lose a superstar, sure it's going to be different,''  
Baker said. ``But you've got to do what you've got to do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bonds, an eight-time All-Star, has been on the disabled list  
just once in his 14-year career. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's tough but we have to go on,'' Javier said. ``We're going  
to miss him. He creates a lot of things for the team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Right-handed rookie pitcher Joe Nathan was called up from  
Double-A Shreveport to fill Bonds' spot on the roster. Nathan was 
scheduled to make his major league debut on Wednesday, starting 
against Marlins right-hander Dennis Springer. 
</P>
<P>
	There had been speculation Bonds might have been injured after  
Friday's brawl with the Diamondbacks, during which Giants third 
baseman Charlie Hayes and Arizona pitcher Todd Stottlemyre got into 
a bench-clearing melee. 
</P>
<P>
	``Let me clear that up right now: Barry told me it was bothering  
him on Friday during batting practice,'' Baker said before Monday's 
game. ``That wasn't it at all, that's 20 years of throwing.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
